    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "warning"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "category" :
    
    
    "Information"
    ,
    
    "consequences" : [
    
    
    
    "The clutch hydraulic system must always be filled or bled using a bleeding device. Furthermore, the bleeder valve must be opened by 1 to 2 turns and the overpressure on the bleeding device must be approx. 1.3 bar (19 psi)."
    ,
    
    
    "Once the filling or bleeding process has started, the clutch pedal must be moved (extremely slowly) into the “Pedal fully depressed” position."
    ,
    
    
    "As there is no system pressure, servo kinematic effects will cause the clutch pedal to move forward abruptly. In order to avoid damage, the pedal must be guided by hand."
    ,
    
    
    "In general, a minimum filling time of 90 seconds must be observed. Once this filling period has elapsed, check that no more bubbles appear at the bleeder valve (use a collecting bottle with transparent hose). Only then should you close the bleeder valve."
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "                     Brake fluid must not come into contact with painted surfaces. If this happens, wash the surface immediately with plenty of                      <b>clean water</b>                     .                 "
    
    }
    
    }
    
    ]
    
    }
    
